@NODE Introduction
@{APEN 3}@{B}Introduction @{ub}@{APEN 1}
~~~~~~~~~~~~
This game is a Flip Screen, Platform, Arcade, Shoot em'up.  You control a bloke, named 'Frank
Finger', around a deadly alien infested planet. You are armed with an upgradable super weapon, which
comes complete with a deadly powerful Grenade launcher.

This game is a sort of 'Turrican' meets 'Worms'.

This is a new updated version with new improved sound, and a few cosmetic changes.  A small number
of people referred to the lack of good sound FX of the original.  Well, not any longer I hope.

@ENDNODE


@NODE Story
@{APEN 3}@{B}THE STORY@{ub}@{APEN 1}
~~~~~~~~~
Death, destruction, pain, misery.  What was once a bright, beautiful planet is now blackend by the
consent invasion of death making Alien bombers.  Plant 'Earth' as it is today. Thousands, if not
millions of innocent lives wiped out with the consent attacks of the war of the Aliens.

There is only one force of resistance who are known as the freedom fighters.  A Earth based force
of defence now crippled with the heavy fire power of the fearsome enemy.  One man stands brave,
'Lt. Frank Finger', one of the few fighters to survive.  He and the others are all sickened of the
site of the aliens near to winning the war.  They prepare to launch one final attack, the final
chance of survival.  If they don't succeed the Earth is doomed.  'Lt. Finger' gathers his men.  He
stands tall and pauses to look at all of his comrades, before saying "They've killed our families,
they've destroyed our world, and they've destroyed our home."

"Now we will do the same to theirs!". . . . . .

@ENDNODE

@NODE "PLAYING THE GAME"
@{APEN 3}@{B}PLAYING THE GAME@{UB}@{APEN 1}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
You play the role of 'Lt. Frank Finger'.  You will be given the task of completing a series of
missions on the alien planet surface.  Your only guide is from Head-Quarters, in touch with them by
micro-radio.  They will brief you on your mission and progress.

On successfully completing a mission, return back to your Space-Ship. To take off, jump into the
cockpit and sit down. The door should close, and the Ship should take off.

On the status bar, at the top of the screen, are the following things:

@{APEN 3}Energy Metre: @{APEN 1}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Each life you start with, you are given 5 energy squares. Every time you get hit you will lose one.
When you have lost all 5 you will loose a life.  More energy can be picked up from alien dead
bodies.

@{APEN 3}Grenades: @{APEN 1}
~~~~~~~~~
On starting a game, you are granted 5 Grenades.  These are used for throwing at aliens.  If timed
right you can kill multiple aliens with one throw.  They can be thrown against certain walls to
destroy them. As well as being able to kill aliens, they can also harm you, so be careful when using
them. More can be picked up from dead alien bodies.

@{APEN 3}Weapon Gauge: @{APEN 1}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Upon starting a game, you are given a low powered basic weapon.  Each time you kill an alien, and
pick up his gun, the gauge is increased by one notch. This does not power up the weapon you are
firing but powers up your next weapon. When you have successfully collected enough guns you will
upgrade to the new weapon. Displayed on the title bar are 3 items:- On the left is your current
weapon which you are firing, on the right is the weapon you will gain if you collect enough alien
guns, and in the middle displays the number of guns you have collected. To upgrade to the very last
weapon, you will have to collect every single alien gun to stand any change of gaining it. This
includes guns in secret bonus rooms as well.

@{APEN 3}Spell Extra: @{APEN 1}
~~~~~~~~~~~~
By picking up letters, and spelling the word EXTRA, a man will appear. Collect this man, and you
will gain an extra life.

@{APEN 3}Men: @{APEN 1}
~~~~
The number of men displayed on the title bar represents the number of lives you currently have.  The
more men you have the better change you have of survival.

@{APEN 3}Score: @{APEN 1}
~~~~~~
Each time you kill something, pick some thing up, or walk onto a new screen, your score will
increase. Score as much as possible to achieve a high score in the high score table. Type in your
name if successful.

Every time you lose a life, your dead body will remain in the game. So every time you play a new
game of 'AFF' you will see where you died. The bodies will also be saved to disk along with your
high scores. The dead bodies and high-scores can be cleared with a option in the main title screen.


@{APEN 3}@{B}Controls:@{APEN 1}@{UB}
~~~~~~~~~
@{i}Joystick: @{ui}
  Left/Right to run
  Up to Jump
  Down to Duck
  Duck and Left/Right to lower gun
  Fire button to fire Weapon
  Hold down fire button for 1 second to throw a grenade.

  Left Mouse button to Quit.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Tips"
@{APEN 3}@{B}General Tips@{APEN 1}@{UB}
~~~~~~~~~~~~
Some levels require you to complete a mission before you can go on to the next, so read each mission
briefing carefully before starting.

Take your time when running around. Steep drops can hurt 'Frank', so take your time when running
down hills or jumping from cliffs.

Use grenades when ever possible, as there are plenty to go around. Grenades can be bounced of walls,
so getting the angle right could kill some aliens out of reach of your normal line of fire. By
jumping and then throwing a grenade will extend the distance it can be thrown.

Search out the levels for secret rooms. Some are easily found while some are not. They contain lots
of goodies from energy to 1-ups.

Try not to miss many guns because as the game gets harder, you will need the best weapon for
survival.

Last of all the best tip is to enjoy your self, and Kill Kill Kill and kill again.

If you think that this game is to easy, and own a A1200, then by pressing the letter 'T' on the
title screen will put the game into turbo mode. This will make the game run twice as fast. This is
for speed freaks.

@endnode
@node "AFF"
@{APEN 3}@{B}Why Alien Fish Finger?@{APEN 1}@{UB}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Well, I had to call it something.  So why 'Alien Fish Finger'?  Well the main hero of this game is
called 'Frank @{B}Finger@{UB}' and on your travels you will come across a person.  I won't tell you
any more, but his name is 'Zaron @{B}Fish@{UB}', a prisoner of the evil @{B}Aliens@{UB}.

Which is why it is called '@{B}Alien Fish Finger@{UB}'.  (I know!! very SAD!!!)

@ENDNODE

